config ZMK_KOREAN_IME_LAYER
    bool "Enable Korean IME-driven layer switching"
    depends on RAW_HID
    default n
    help
      Listens for Raw HID packets (marker 0xD5) reporting the Korean
      IME state from a host application and switches between two
      configured layers accordingly.

      Pair with korean-ime-reporter-windows (or any host app that
      speaks the same protocol) running on the connected PC.
